        <h2>How can you convince your parents to get a horse? I've always
LOOOOOOOOOVED horses!</h2>
        <p>I can´t tell you how to convince your parents to get a horse. I wish I had a recipe so I could tell you how. I was so lucky that my mom rode and that later on, I got my own horse. If you join a riding school, you can have the same contact with the horses, and they would probably like it if you helped with the daily chores. The most important thing is to enjoy your time with the horses. The horse will love you the same if you own him or just take care of him.</p>

        <h2>What made you so interested in horses? Do you plan to get any other horses? Are you going to become a pro horse rider when you grow up?</h2>
        <p>I don´t know what made me so interested in horses, it´s difficult for me to answer because it´s all about the horses I like. I started riding when I was 3-years-old and I have been riding ever since. I like the company of the horses, they are so mild and loving if you take good care of them.
It´s really hard to become a pro rider, it costs a lot of money and time and you have to have a really good horse to go all the way and last but not least you have to have a little luck. I wish I had the funds and time for it but I don´t. The closest I have been to pro level has been with my horse Rozolino. Next time we move up it´s for national competitions, I really, really hope that happens.</p>
        
        <h2>Have you ever fallen off a horse? How many times?</h2>
        <p>I don´t know how many times I have fallen. I have been riding since I was 3-years-old so I stopped counting many years ago.
My old riding teacher once told me that to be a good rider you had to fall 100 times, so I still need to fall a few more times before I’m really good.
Even though I have fallen many times I have never broken anything or been badly injured.</p>   

